llm_text: Euthyroid sick syndrome is a type of disorder classified under both syndromic disease and thyroid gland disorder. It is identified with the database reference "MONDO:0006755" and is part of the OTAR subset. The syndrome has multiple database cross-references, including DOID:2856, EFO:1000931, ICD10CM:E07.81, ICD9:790.94, MEDGEN:41908, MESH:D005067, MedDRA:10015549, NCIT:C113170, SCTID:237542005, and UMLS:C0015190. In terms of matching, it has close matches with 10015549 and exact matches with 237542005, 41908, c0015190, d005067, doid_2856, e07.81, and ncit_c113170. The disorder is characterized by abnormal thyroid function tests, specifically low triiodothyronine and elevated reverse triiodothyronine, in the context of non-thyroidal illness. It is also known by the synonyms "euthyroid sick syndrome," "sick euthyroid syndrome," and "sick-euthyroid syndrome."

llm_text: Ellis-van Creveld syndrome is a condition that exhibits a combination of features including short stature, postaxial polydactyly, ectodermal dysplasia, and congenital heart defects. It is classified under several categories such as autosomal recessive disease, cardiogenetic disease, ectodermal dysplasia syndrome, and Jeune syndrome. This condition is identified with the identifier MONDO:0009162 and is associated with various databases and references like DOID:12714, GARD:1301, ICD9:756.55, MEDGEN:8584, MESH:D004613, MedDRA:10008724, NCIT:C84684, NORD:1083, OMIM:225500, Orphanet:289, SCTID:62501005, and UMLS:C0013903. It also has several exact synonyms including Chondroectodermal dysplasia, EVC, Ellis Van Creveld Syndrome, Ellis Van Creveld syndrome, Ellis-VAN Creveld syndrome, Ellis-van Creveld syndrome, Mesoectodermal dysplasia, and mesodermic dysplasia. For more information, you can visit the link provided: https://rarediseases.info.nih.gov/diseases/1301/ellis-van-creveld-syndrome.
